---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Technology — Tech Terms That Score"
  description="Technology words valid in Scrabble with scoring. PIXEL 14pts, BYTES 10pts, MODEM 10pts, PROXY 17pts. Tech vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble technology words, pixel scrabble points, bytes scrabble, modem scrabble word, tech words scrabble, computer terms scrabble valid, digital words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Technology — Tech Terms That Score","description":"Technology words valid in Scrabble with scoring. PIXEL 14pts, BYTES 10pts, MODEM 10pts, PROXY 17pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-technology"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is PIXEL a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! PIXEL scores 14 points (P=3, I=1, X=8, E=1, L=1). Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. The X=8 tile makes this a high-value 5-letter word."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is BYTES valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. BYTES scores 10 points (B=3, Y=4, T=1, E=1, S=1). The plural of BYTE is accepted in competitive Scrabble."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What technology words are valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Many tech words are valid: PIXEL (14pts), PROXY (17pts), BYTES (10pts), MODEM (10pts), CODEC (12pts), CYBER (12pts), VIRUS (8pts). Newer terms like WIFI and URL are not yet valid."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Technology — Tech Terms That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Technology has given Scrabble a treasure trove of valid words. From PIXEL to BYTES, tech vocabulary features X, Y, and mid-value consonants that deliver solid scores. The trick is knowing which modern terms have made it into the official dictionary.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PROXY (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">14 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PIXEL</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">CYBER</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">10 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MODEM</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">High-Scoring Tech Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">PROXY — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">P=3, R=1, O=1, X=8, Y=4 · 5 letters · Uses X tile</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">An intermediary server or agent. PROXY's X=8 and Y=4 deliver 12 points from just two tiles. The remaining PRO costs only 5 points in tiles but positions the word perfectly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💻 PIXEL</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · P=3, I=1, X=8, E=1, L=1 · Screen dot</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💻 CYBER</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · C=3, Y=4, B=3, E=1, R=1 · Digital realm</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💻 CODEC</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · C=3, O=1, D=2, E=1, C=3 · Encoder/decoder</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">💻 BYTES</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · B=3, Y=4, T=1, E=1, S=1 · Data units</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Reliable Tech Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MODEM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VIRUS</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">DIODE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">LASER</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RADAR</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TOKEN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Tech Words NOT Valid in Scrabble</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10"><p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Invalid Tech Words</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WIFI, URL, HTML, USB, GPS, APP, EMOJI, SELFIE — acronyms and very new coinages</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Surprisingly Valid</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BYTE, PIXEL, CODEC, MODEM, CURSOR, GLITCH, AVATAR, MATRIX, BINARY, CIPHER</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Tech Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">PIXEL on TLS:</span> Place the X on Triple Letter Score for X=24 alone. PIXEL then scores 30 points from a 5-letter word.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BYTES as rack clearer:</span> B=3 and Y=4 are tiles players struggle with. BYTES clears both plus T, E, S — leaving your rack clean.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">MODEM for M doubles:</span> Holding two M tiles? MODEM (M=3, O=1, D=2, E=1, M=3 = 10pts) uses both Ms efficiently.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Tech words that entered English <span class="text-white font-medium">before ~2000</span> are almost always valid (MODEM, PIXEL, LASER, VIRUS). Newer terms (WIFI, APP, EMOJI) often haven't been added. Stick to words describing hardware or established concepts.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words in Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/new-words-added-2026/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">New Words Added 2026</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/science-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Science Words in Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Verify any tech term instantly — free Scrabble word checker, no sign-up needed</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
